        HOME B2 THE STRAITS TIMES SATURDAY, AUGUST 8, 2020 | | | MORNING SEGMENT Watch live on www.straitstim­es.com, free-to-air TV channels or the NDPeeps YouTube channel Flag fly-past Parade at the Padang and the Anthem Moment Roar of Unity NDP2020 will begin with Prime Minister Lee Hsien Loong’s National Day message, followed by a parade at the Padang reviewed by President Halimah Yacob.
The state flag will be raised concurrent­ly across different locations and Madam Halimah will lead the nation in singing the National Anthem during the Anthem Moment.
The parade will salute front-line and essential workers in appreciati­on of their efforts in combating Covid-19, and the presidenti­al gun salute will be held on the Padang field. Six F-15SG Eagle fighter jets from the Republic of Singapore Air Force will execute the Roar of Unity aerial display over the Padang and fly over the eastern part of Singapore before swinging around to the west. Maritime sail-past Red Lions Mobile column Vessels from Republic of Singapore Navy, the Police Coast Guard, the Singapore Civil Defence Force and the Maritime and Port Authority will execute a sail-past along Marina Barrage. Key assets from the Singapore Armed Forces and the Home Team will reach into the heartland along five routes to allow viewers to experience the iconic mobile column from their homes. For the first time, the Red Lions will parachute down in heartland areas in Jurong East and Sengkang, paying tribute to front-line and essential workers at Ng Teng Fong General and Sengkang General hospitals. NOTE:
The Red Lions will land at the hospitals around 9am and the footage will be shown at 11.10am. Watch live on www.straitstim­es.com, free-to-air TV channels or the NDPeeps YouTube channel Time Event Details STATE FLAG F-15 FIGHTER JET The fly-past will feature two state flags being flown by helicopter over heartland areas for the first time. The fly-past – the longest one to date – will take place over heartland areas for the first time in NDP history. Hospital pass Heartland pass SELETAR EXPRESSWAY Sembawang Air Base Western route SELETAR EXPRESSWAY Khoo Teck Puat Hospital Eastern route TAMPINES EXPRESSWAY Sengkang General Hospital TAMPINES EXPRESSWAY BUKIT TIMAH EXPRESSWAY BUKIT TIMAH EXPRESSWAY Tan Tock Seng Hospital Ng Teng Fong General Hospital Changi General Hospital The Padang AYER RAJAH EXPRESSWAY PAN-ISLAND EXPRESSWAY PAN-ISLAND EXPRESSWAY The Padang AYER RAJAH EXPRESSWAY START START National University Hospital START Singapore General Hospital Alexandra Hospital Sembawang NORTH-EASTERN ROUTE NORTHERN ROUTE Woodlands FIREWORKS RED LIONS AND MOBILE COLUMN Sembawang Woodlands Marsiling Admiralty Yishun WESTERN ROUTE SELETAR EXPRESSWAY Khatib 1 NOTE: Areas drawn are indicative. Yew Tee Seletar Punggol Punggol Yew Tee TAMPINES EXPRESSWAY Yio Chu Kang Choa Chu Kang Sengkang Pasir Ris Buangkok Bukit Batok Bukit Panjang Ang Mo Kio Ang Mo Kio Bishan
